This paper is about video segmentation using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also discusses the use of semi-supervised learning, which involves leveraging unlabeled data, and the use of temporal information, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses the CityScapes dataset, which is a popular dataset for image and video segmentation tasks, and could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on video segmentation could also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as robots often need to perceive and segment their environment in real-time.
